DESCRIPTION
Hardening audit finding (med; DoS/OOM). The three external-process paths -- exec_runner.go:117, exec_generator.go:113, eval/exec_judge.go:146 -- rely solely on the passed ctx with no deadline, and read the script's ETUDE_OUTPUT_FILE fully into memory (exec_runner.go:142) with no size cap. A hung script blocks forever; a runaway script emitting a multi-GB output OOMs. Add a configurable timeout (ctx deadline) and an output-size limit to all three. Env hygiene, non-zero-exit handling, and Lstat output checks are already correct.

