## Implement

**Implemented:**
- Added `Timeout time.Duration` field to ExecRunner, ExecGenerator, ExecJudge. When > 0, wraps ctx with `context.WithTimeout` BEFORE `exec.CommandContext`. Zero = unlimited (backward compat).
- Added `MaxOutputBytes int64` field to ExecRunner, ExecGenerator, ExecJudge. When > 0, uses `io.LimitReader(f, max+1)` after file open for a TOCTOU-safe hard cap. Cheap `fi.Size()` pre-check also applied. Zero = unlimited.
- FIX A (WaitDelay): Set `cmd.WaitDelay = <pkg>WaitDelay` (10s const) on all three exec paths BEFORE `cmd.Run()`. Bounds pipe-drain after ctx fires or process exits.
- FIX B (LimitReader): Replaced bare `os.ReadFile(outputPath)` with `io.LimitReader`-based read in all three paths when `MaxOutputBytes > 0`.
- ctx-taxonomy error: DeadlineExceeded → "timed out after Xdur" (keeps %w wrap); Canceled → "context done" (unchanged).
- CLI defaults: `Timeout: 10*time.Minute`, `MaxOutputBytes: 64<<20` applied in resolveRunner (replay, bench), resolveJudge (bench), NewExecGenerator (retro). Added `--timeout` DurationVar flag to replay, bench, retro generate commands. bench --timeout applies to BOTH ExecRunner AND ExecJudge.
